{
  "number": 1813,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1813",
  "title": "Query params should be omitted when possible for cleaner URLs",
  "body": "This is a followup to https://github.com/yarnpkg/website/pull/322#issuecomment-270567447\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nA little bit of both. ⚡️ 🐞 ⚡️ \r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nConducting a search on [yarnpkg.com/search](https://yarnpkg.com/search) adds unneeded query params to the URL:  `?q=fetch&p=0&is_v=1`\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nQuery should just be `q=fetch` by default, and only include the `p` and `is_v` values when their values are something other than their defaults.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\n\r\nAll browsers. 🌍 \r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\n\r\nCleaner URLs are easier to read, edit, and share.",
